On ROS2 Foxy we subscribe to /points but lose ~5% of messages under load.
Which DDS (Fast-DDS vs Cyclone) do you recommend, and what QoS profile for se=
nsor_data?

---
Reply:
Use RELIABLE only for low-rate commands; for pointclouds prefer BEST_EFFORT w=
ith history depth 5=E2=80=9310. Cyclone DDS often behaves better on congested=
 Wi=E2=80=91Fi; on wired LAN tune recv buffer sizes per our tuning guide.
